<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7180> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7180" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText ". . . . . II f., Pr., uncertain date. The name and title in an inscription found at Miletus is reported as follows: ....# | ...# (Milet. 1.2.118, no. 14). M. Segre proposes the reading # and associates him with the M'. Laterensis (see above) who is named on inscriptions of Kalymnos (Ann. Scuola Arch. Atene 22/23, 1952,  158ff., nos. 130A, B, C, D, and E; AEpig. 1940, no. 129), but, if the report in Milet. that the lower bar of the  first # is' clearly preserved is correct, Segre's identification can hardly stand. We would then have another  senator of praetorian rank in the first century, perhaps a Terentius.[225]\n" .
